  "monologue": "High-level rationale: The user has strong evening cue sensitivity and a very high need for structure. A small, reliable post-pause ritual reinforces automatic, non-food coping and reduces impulsivity, nudging toward steady, predictable evenings without increasing cognitive load.",
  "utterance": "Nice work staying with the plan. After your pause tonight, try a simple post-pause ritual: spend 1 minute doing a body scan to notice any tension, 1 minute of focused breathing to reset, then a quick 30-second light stretch, and log the ritual. Keeping this ritual ultra-simple helps make it automatic on busy or stressful evenings. If hunger resurfaces later, have a small yogurt with berries and log it.",
